The White House Office of the Press Secretary recently held a press briefing with Press Secretary Josh Earnest, Secretary of Commerce Penny Pritzker, Deputy National Security Advisor Ben Rhodes, Counselor to the President John Podesta, and CEO of MasterCard Ajay Banga. The briefing covered a range of topics, including efforts to engage the US and India business communities, the expansion of the US-India Strategic Dialogue, the announcement of the US-India CEO Forum, and the progress made in the US-India relationship. The briefing also touched on the civil nuclear agreement between the US and India, the importance of protecting intellectual property, the US-India defense relationship, and the ongoing counterterrorism efforts against ISIS. The briefing concluded with a discussion on the President's upcoming visit to Saudi Arabia.